{
  "stem": "150.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He is married to Shirley, a very nice young lady who comes from South Carolina, of all places.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I have a grandchild by the name of Nicholas who is 12.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He'll be bar mitzvah next year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I have an eight-year-old little girl named Rachel, and we get along very nicely.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my younger son, Larry, he's 37, and he lives in Pittsburgh.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he's not married.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was married, as a matter of fact, to a concentration camp survivor about 20 years ago-- 15 years ago-- and the daughter of a survivor.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Her father had been in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it turned out to be a terrible, terrible thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it sort of soured him on marriage for a long time and just about destroyed his life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I might parenthetically say that once upon a long time ago, I had a conversation in my kitchen with Dennis Prager, who is a man I respect who has got the radio program, wrote a number of books.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, his book about the eight-- nine questions people ask about Judaism, we translated into Russian, distributed thousands, tens of thousands of copies throughout the Soviet Union and also among the immigrants here.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Dennis was telling me that when he was a younger man, his first job as a summer camp-- a Jewish summer camp-- counselor, the director of the camp assembled all of the counselors the night before the camp was opened.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said to them, I just want to warn you, those of you who have not been counselors before, there's two categories of kids that you're almost sure to have problems with-- children of rabbis and children of survivors.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Dennis said he doesn't know why that is, and I don't know why that is.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
